shapes.name: Text 17
shapes.text: Keep compositions primarily monochromatic to maintain cohesion. Primary colors can be used freely in any composition. Secondary colors may also dominate when appropriate, but only from a single spectrum—never mix secondaries from multiple spectrums within the same composition.

shapes.name: Text 3
shapes.text:
The MAI monogram is the brand’s primary logo. 

Simple in form yet distinctive in character, its letterforms are rooted in Segoe Sans but reimagined with subtle flared terminals and stroke contrast, bringing a humanist quality that’s unique within the category. This blend of familiar structure and nuanced detail balances precision with warmth, reflecting the brand’s core duality: technological sophistication paired with a deeply human perspective.

The overall shape, weight, and spacing of the monogram allow it to hold its clarity and presence at smaller sizes—particularly when contained in a circle or square format

shapes.name: Text 1
shapes.text:
The Microsoft AI wordmark serves as the secondary logo for the MAI brand. This mark should only be used within internal communications, presentations, team swag, and partners inside the company but is not intended for external-facing use.

The wordmark is an extension of the custom letterforms created for the monogram. Based on the structure and proportions of Segoe Sans, yet refined with the subtle humanist flared stems and shift in stroke width. Together, the marks allow for a flexible identity system, expanding or contracting as needed.

shapes.name: Text 4
shapes.text:
The monogram may be paired next to a text block to create tertiary logo lockups, like the examples provided on this page. These are reserved for internal-facing applications such as swag, apparel, and event materials and not for external brand communications. They provide a space for personality and play within the identity system.

The underlying structure is based on a four-line text block that aligns to the baseline of the monogram. This format offers flexibility, allowing the logo to adapt to different contexts while maintaining its core structure.

shapes.name: Text 3
shapes.text: Always ensure the MAI logo is clear, legible, and unobstructed in every application. Whether placed over a solid color, pattern, or image, maintain strong contrast and minimize visual distractions. The logo should stand as a distinct, recognizable focal point within the composition.
